1986;;My Little Girl;;American;;Connie Kaiserman;;Mary Stuart Masterson, James Earl Jones, Geraldine Chaplin;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/My_Little_Girl;;Franny Bettinger (Masterson) has had a privileged and wealthy upbringing. One summer she takes a job at a halfway house where she finds herself personally affected by the people she meets. Despite facing hostility due to her background, Bettinger becomes determined to teach the youngsters that they are important and can succeed in life. Unfortunately, she faces opposition from her parents and from her supervisor.